<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN229-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. kōccēramāṉ yāṉaikkaṭcēy māntarañcēralirumpoṟai iṉṉanāḷiṟṟuñcumeṉa añci avaṉ tuñciyaviṭattuk kūṭalūrkiḻār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN229">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>āṭiya laḻaṟkuṭṭat</l>
<l>tāriru ḷaraiyiraviṉ</l>
<l>muṭappaṉaiyattu vērmutalāk</l>
<l>kaṭaikkuḷattuk kayaṅkāyap</l>
<l>paṅkuṉi yuyaraḻuvattut</l>
<l>talaināṇmī ṉilaitiriya</l>
<l>nilaināṇmī ṉataṉetirērtarat</l>
<l>toṉṉāṇmīṉ ṟuṟaipaṭiyap</l>
<l>pācic cellā tūci muṉṉā</l>
<l>taḷakkarttiṇai viḷakkākak</l>
<l>kaṉaiyeri parappak kāletirpu poṅki</l>
<l>yorumīṉ vīḻntaṉṟāl vicumpi ṉāṉē</l>
<l>yatukaṇ, ṭiyāmum piṟarum palvē ṟiravalar</l>
<l>paṟaiyicai yaruvi naṉṉāṭṭup poruna</l>
<l>ṉōyila ṉāyi ṉaṉṟumaṟ ṟilleṉa</l>
<l>vaḻinta neñca maṭiyuḷam parappa</l>
<l>vañciṉa meḻunāḷ vantaṉ ṟiṉṟē</l>
<l>maintuṭai yāṉai kaivait tuṟaṅkavun</l>
<l>tiṇpiṇi muracaṅ kaṇkiḻin turuḷavuṅ</l>
<l>kāval veṇkuṭai kālparin tulaṟavuṅ</l>
<l>kāliyaṟ kalimāk katiyila vaikavu</l>
<l>mēlō rulaka meytiṉa ṉākali</l>
<l>ṉoṇṟoṭi makaḷirk kuṟutuṇai yākit</l>
<l>taṉṟuṇai yāya maṟantaṉaṉ kollō</l>
<l>pakaivarp piṇikku māṟṟa ṉacaivark</l>
<l>kaḷantukoṭai yaṟiyā vīkai</l>
<l>maṇivarai yaṉṉa māa yōṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="2">In the middle of the night in difficult darkness, </l>
<l corresp="1">in a pot of fire whose nature is dancing, </l>
<l corresp="3">while, with the root of the crooked palmyra tree as a base, </l>
<l corresp="4">the deep of the pond was hot to the limit, </l>
<l corresp="5">while in the high depth of Phalguni </l>
<l corresp="6">the star on the first day did not move from [its] position, </l>
<l corresp="7">while against it rose the star in the stable day, </l>
<l corresp="8">while the star on the old day sank into the ghat, </l>
<l corresp="9">not going east, not approaching north, </l>
<l corresp="10">as the lamp of the ocean clan </l>
<l corresp="11">while dense darkness spread, facing the time, boiling, </l>
<l corresp="12">a star fell down indeed from the sky. </l>
<l corresp="13">Seeing that, we and others [and] many different beggars </l>
<l>said “the fighter of the good land with waterfalls that sound [like] drums, </l>
<l>if he were without pain it would be good”, (14f.)</l>
<l corresp="16">[and] while desolate hearts spread in [our] constricted insides, </l>
<l corresp="17">seven days came with us in fear. Today, </l>
<l corresp="18">while the mighty elephant put down [its] trunk [and] slumbered, </l>
<l corresp="19">while the drum with taught straps tore [its] eye rolling, </l>
<l corresp="20">while the protective white parasol broke [its] handle [and] withered, </l>
<l corresp="21">while the spirited horses that move [like] the wind kept without motion, </l>
<l corresp="22">because he reached the world of those above, </l>
<l corresp="23">being [now] the consort had by women with bright bracelets, </l>
<l corresp="24">did he forget the group of his own consorts? </l>
<l corresp="27">– the one dark like a sapphire mountain, </l>
<l corresp="26">[who was] giving [gifts] that did not know of giving by measure </l>
<l corresp="25">to those who yearned [for them], he capable of tying down the enemies. </l>
</lg>
